-- Saudi British Bank Third-Quarter Net Declines 26% as Provisions Increase
-- B y   S h a j i   M a t h e w
-- 2010-10-12T13:24:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/saudi-british-bank-third-quarter-net-declines-26-as-provisions-increase.html
Saudi British Bank, the lender 40
percent owned by HSBC Holdings Plc, said third-quarter profit
fell to 419 million riyals from 570 million riyals in the year-
earlier period because of provisions. The bank made the
announcement to the Saudi bourse today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  